main event: A UFO sighting was reported near the Homestead Air Force Base in Florida on 30th May 1956, observed by multiple witnesses for about 40 minutes before disappearing.
interesting points: The object was described as bright or luminous, either circular, elliptical, or spherical in shape, and estimated to be between 30 and 60 feet in diameter.
It appeared to hover before flying off at a rapid rate of speed, and it showed varying intensity and velocity, as well as sudden changes in direction.
Observers could not hear any sound emanating from the object, and some attempted to identify it using binoculars but could only see a red light.
The object was observed by pilots, USAF personnel, and air traffic controllers, adding credibility to the report.
The sighting details include the object's estimated altitude, speed, and changes in altitude over a short period of time, as well as the hazy but clear evening weather conditions during the sighting.
